review_blob: on tap at horsebrass. sweet and carmelly with a touch of citrusy hops.  pretty light tasting and deceiving in alcohol content. very tasty.

nice dark brown/black pour..  aroma of licorice, coffee, etc.  medium mouthfeel.  somewhat sour flavor. not much bitterness. lots of coffee, roastiness in there. very tasty and the alcohol is very well concealed. very good and moylans continues to impress me.

red/amber pour with a big frothy head. smells kinda earthy and malty.  nice and moderately malty, with a sweet caramel taste, with a touch of hops to balance. not the greatest, but widely available and pretty tasty when I dont want an abrasive IPA or something.
amber/gold color with a nice soapy white head. hoppy aroma. sweet and sorta carmamely with a moderately bitter citrus finish. pretty good.
dark red pour with tan/white frothy head. nice malty aroma with citrus hop notes.  mellow malty body with a touch of citrus in the finish. very drinkable and tasty.

brown pour with little head. dry raisin and caramel in the aroma. tastes dry, with strong caramel malt flavor, and quite a bitter resiny hop finish. pretty good but not up to par with most barleywines ive had.
amber/orange pour, white head. citrusy hop aroma. tastes the same as it smells. better than im used to from deschutes.

clear amber pour, with a small whitish head. sweet malty aroma. sweet, caramel malt flavor, with a touch of hops to make it not too sweet. pretty full mouthfeel. i have drank this beer so many times. and it is good. great for when I dont want an abrasive hoppy beer.
orange pour, white head. citrusy hop aroma. pretty straightforward ipa, with mostly citrus hop bitterness. better than I expected from pyramid.
straw pour with white head. sort of sweet smelling. corny tasting, no bitterness, pretty watery. not so bad to wash down my barbecue chicken and mac with.
light amber pour, clean white head. sweet malt aroma, with some citrus too. light bodied, well balanced, good citrus hop finish. a nice pale ale.
clear light amber pour, frothy white head. lots of pine/grass hops in the aroma.  very clean tasting with some good earthy notes, with crisp hoppy finish.  a great IPA.

2006 bottle. pours nearly black, with a little tan head. aroma is lots of bourbon, and a little alcohol. great coffee/chocolate malt flavored base with vanilla, oak, and licorice notes. finishes with bourbon and roast flavors. alcohol is pretty well concealed. very tasty, and Im glad I found some before it was all gone.
beer_name: Full Sail Black Gold Imperial Stout Bourbon Barrel Aged

review_blob: dark black with red tint in my glass, with a cm or two of tan foam.  sweet roasty malt aroma with some hops in there too.  chocolatey, roasty base of flavor with citrusy hops to balance.  full mouthfeel with soft carbonation.  i usually dont like porters that much but this one is very good.

clear gold/amber pour, with almost no head. sweet and fruity aroma. crisp flavor, sweet and spicy with some alcohol in there. nice full mouthfeel. a little less extreme than I expected but pretty good nonetheless.
dark brown, clear pour, a little head. aroma is all roasted malt. big nice sweet malt flavored with a slight twinge of alcohol in the finish. pretty tasty.
dark amber pour, soapy white head. C-hop aroma. sweet malt base with a decent enough touch of hops to end it. medium bodied. pretty good but not that great
good solid IPA.  golden amber pour with a white soapy head. citrusy hop aroma mostly . sweet malt base, with a great bitter finish. nice medium mouthfeel and very tasty.

had this at widmer gasthaus. dark near black pour, with a small tan head. smells like an IS. roasty and coffee-y.  full mouthfeel. lots of chocolate coffee and roast malt in there. slightly hoppy and alcoholic finish. a pretty good IS, very drinkable.
beer_name: Widmer Brothers KGB Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: light hazy gold pour, with a fine white head. hoppy sweet aroma. tastes kind of like a hopped witbier. spicy, grassy, light, with a good touch of hops to finish. decent but not great.
pours dark brown color. no head to speak of really. sweet fruity smelling. at first this was good, vinous, sweet but not too sweet, but i was sick of it by the end of my glass.
pours a nice golden color, with a lasting white head. tart, fruity, and sort of spicy. pretty sweet but enough bitterness/bite in it to balance it nicely.

on tap. dark red pour, small lacey whitish head. malty, spicy aroma. flavor is very malty, with caramel and spice notes. decent amount of hops to finish it off. medium mouthfeel. i definitely dont mind drinking this one.

nice dark amber pour, and a tiny white soapy head. citrusy hop aroma. well balanced flavor with a good malty base with  a bit of citrusy hops. medium mouthfeel and very drinkable. i want to try this on cask sometime.
dark brown pour with a light head.  roastymalt aroma.  sweet caramel and roasty coffee flavors, not bad but im not feeling this one. somewhat sharp mouthfeel.
beer_name: JosephsBrau Black Toad Distinctive Dark Ale

review_blob: dark brown pour, little tan head.  anise,  malt aroma.  chocolate, anise, a little sharpness appear in the flavors.  somewhat light bodied and a little too carbonated for my tastes.
amber pour, white head sweet floral hop aroma. pretty mild for an ipa. very sweet, with not that much hop bitterness. pretty good but I dont know if ill get it again.
ambery pour with a white head. it was dark. hoppy aroma. sweet undertones with loads of C hops in there. full to medium bodiet. not great but very solid, and I get it frequently.

opaque black pour, big tan head which shrinks and stays at 1cm or so. roasty malt aroma, with some chocolate in there too. quite full bodied mouthfeel. taste is on the roasty side, with lots of coffee, chocolate, etc. a decent kick of hops in there too to break things up. a nice lasting roasty bitter aftertaste. a great beer and a great bargain too.
beer_name: Bear Republic Big Bear Black Stout

review_blob: one of the nicest looking pours ive seen. huge tan-off white rocky head on top of a clear dark brown with a tinge of red in it.  fruity, yeasty, alcohol and sweet aroma.  caramel/dark fruit/earthy flavor, with a slight amount of alcohol  warmth and flavor(def. doesnt seem 11%).  very smooth and full mouthfeel. cant say anthing bad about this one.
orange/amber pour,  big head, which disappeared sorta quickly. hoppy sweet aroma. flavor is very sweet and malty, but with a good floral hop flavor to give it some bite.  a lot like an IPA.

clear red/brown pour, fast disappearing white head. raisiny, sweet, malty aroma. flavors the same--sweet, fruity, and a tiny amount of bitterness to balance it.  medium bodied, and very drinkable. pretty good.

dark brown pour, small fizzy whtie/tan head. aroma is caramelly malt, sweet, little alcohol. good fruity/sweet malty flavor, a little yeasty and spicy too.a  little alcohol felt.. full bodied. very tasty.
dark cloudy brown pour, lots of off-white frothy head. sweet dark fruit aroma.  spicy, mild sweetness, raisiny flavor. good light carbonated mouthfeel. not bad!

beer_brewer_name: Hair of the Dog Brewing Company
review_blob: on tap at horsebrass. tastes way different than i remember it from bottles ive had. hazy dark amber pour, small white head. aroma is alcohol, spicy, lots of bananas. lots of bananas in the flavor as well, good yeasty, fruity sweet, spicy flavor, with a good alcohol bite. nice full mouthfeel.
dark brown pour, large off-white head. aroma of fruit, sweet malt. taste is sweet, tart, earthy. very dry, pretty good but wont get again.
brown, sorta hazy pour. fizzy whiteish  head.  caramelly, sweet aroma. taste was pretty one dimensional--sweet, sorta fruity. full mouthfeel. decent but not great.
amber pour, lasting, lacy white head.  sweet aroma, lots of hops.  sweet, syrupy caramel backbone, with a decent bite of piney/floral hops. a little too sweet for me, but a pretty good IPA.

had this at horsebrass.  dark red pour, tan head. hoppy floral aroma, a little bit of caramel in there.  sweet, caramelly, little spicy, finishing pretty dang hoppy somewhat alcoholic. full mouthfeel. a good strong ale.

had this at the rose and raindrop as well. i love the regular homo erectus.  gold/amber color, off-white head. aroma of hops, caramel, wood.  full bodied, strong malt/caramel/woody and sweet base with huge hop finish. better than regular? i dont know, but it was good.
beer_name: Walking Man Bourbon Barrel Homo Erectus Imperial IPA

review_blob: had this at OBF. amber pour, with a light head. malty aroma, a little hops in there too.  decently full mouthfeel, caramelly malt base and a good bite from the piney hops to balance it. this was ok but pretty "meh"
beer_name: Pizza Port Shark Bitten Double Red Ale

review_blob: my first saison. amber color, small white frothy head.  fruity, sort of sour aroma. flavor was somewhat spicy, sour, and light.  makes me want to try more in this style.
dark amber pour, with a white head.  great piney aroma, some alcohol, resiny sweetness. a nice full bodied, balanced (for a iipa), strong ale.  i love double ipas and this is a good example of one

had this at a fest. dark red pour, tan head. aroma is woody, lots of hops, nutty/caramel. flavor is a good caramel malt underside with oak note with a strong hop presence, especially in the finish. full mouthfeel. regular AB is one of my go-to beers, and this just adds to it a little. if only it was available in small bottles.

had this at a festival. i was expecting this to be overpowering but it wasnt, for 18%. opaque black with a little tan head. aroma of coffee, alcohol. nice full mouthfeel, and a huge amount of flavor. alcohol, some fruits (raisiny, etc), coffee, chocolate. Im glad i finally tried this. tastes more like 10%, which I think is perfect for an IS.
hazy brown color, little head. smells of yeast, and a bit of fruit. flavor is yeasty, fruity-banana, etc,  with a bit of a spicy finish. medium bodied. very tasty
dark amber pour, with off-whtie frothy, long-lasting head.  piney hops in flavor and nose, caramel undertones. seems to be missing something. decent nonetheless. good thick mouthfeel though.
"black brutal" dark pour, tan head. hoppy aroma. sightly roasty malt undertones with good citrus bitterness over it and in the finish. medium bodied, very good

beer_brewer_name: Hair of the Dog Brewing Company
review_blob: cloudy gold pour with a nice frothy white head. aroma is citrusy hops. flavor is  pretty balanced sweet undertones and a good citrus bitterness.
beer_name: Hair of the Dog Blue Dot Double IPA

review_blob: clear golden pour, with an inch or so of frothy white head. aroma is sharp, piney hops. flavor is mildly sweet with piney/grassy hops.  medium mouthfeel. a decent IPA, but i can think of tons id rather have.
